    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIf a call to `vim.lsp.buf.format()` results in no change in the buffer contents, diagnostics that were previously visible for the buffer are hidden.\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\n```lua\r\nlocal pattern = \"lua\"\r\nlocal cmd = { \"/path/to/bin/lua-language-server\" }\r\n-- Add files/folders here that indicate the root of a project\r\nlocal root_markers = { \".git\", \".editorconfig\" }\r\n-- Change to table with settings if required\r\nlocal settings = {\r\n  runtime = { version = \"LuaJIT\", path = vim.split(package.path, \";\") },\r\n  workspace = { library = { vim.env.VIMRUNTIME }, checkThirdParty = false },\r\n}\r\n\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"FileType\", { pattern = pattern,\r\n  callback = function(args)\r\n    local match = vim.fs.find(root_markers, { path = args.file, upward = true })[1]\r\n    local root_dir = match and vim.fn.fnamemodify(match, \":p:h\") or nil\r\n    vim.lsp.start({ name = \"bugged-ls\", cmd = cmd, root_dir = root_dir, settings = settings })\r\n  end,\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\n1. Load Neovim with this init.lua, then open a Lua file with the contents `local x =  y`.\r\n2. Observe that diagnostics appear.\r\n3. Run `:lua vim.lsp.buf.format()`\r\n4. Observe that the file is formatted (extra space is removed) and diagnostics reappear.\r\n5. Run `:lua vim.lsp.buf.format()`\r\n6. Observe that the file is unchanged and the diagnostics disappear.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe diagnostics do not disappear when the file is unchanged by reformatting.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.9.1\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nLuaLS 3.7.0 (but this is a Neovim bug)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
